---------------------------------------------------------------------------
✅ 1️⃣ getArguments()
👉 Kya karta hai:-
Workflow ko jo input mila hai (UI / request / previous step se) wo return karta hai.
Type → Map<String, Object>

✅ Code:-
Map args = context.getArguments();

System.out.println("Arguments: " + args);
🟢 Output:-
Arguments: {identity=john.doe, role=EmployeeRole, requestId=12345}
💡 Real Use:-
Role, identity, form fields yahi se milte hain,
Har workflow step isi se data uthata hai.

✅ 2️⃣ setArguments()
👉 Kya karta hai:-
Workflow ke arguments ko update ya replace karta hai,
Next steps ko data pass karne ke liye use hota hai.

✅ Code:-
Map args = context.getArguments();

args.put("approvalStatus", "APPROVED");

context.setArguments(args);
🟢 Output:-
Arguments updated: {identity=john.doe, role=EmployeeRole, approvalStatus=APPROVED}

💡 Real Use:-
Approval ke baad status pass karna

✅ 3️⃣ getExecutionResult()
👉 Kya karta hai:-
Workflow execution ka final result return karta hai.

✅ Code:-
Object result = context.getExecutionResult();
System.out.println("Execution Result: " + result);
🟢 Output:-
Execution Result: SUCCESS

✅ 4️⃣ getLastExecutionStatus():-
👉 Kya karta hai:-
Last executed step ka status return karta hai.

✅ Code:-
String status = context.getLastExecutionStatus();

System.out.println("Last Step Status: " + status);
🟢 Output:-
Last Step Status: COMPLETED

✅ 5️⃣ getExecutionTime():-
👉 Kya karta hai:-
Workflow ko run hone me kitna time laga (milliseconds me)

✅ Code:-
long time = context.getExecutionTime();

System.out.println("Execution Time: " + time + " ms");
🟢 Output:-
Execution Time: 1523 ms
-----------------------------------------------
🔥 Full Combined Example (WorkflowContext):-
// 1. Get arguments
Map args = context.getArguments();
System.out.println("Args: " + args);

// 2. Update arguments
args.put("processed", true);
context.setArguments(args);

// 3. Get execution result
Object result = context.getExecutionResult();
System.out.println("Result: " + result);

// 4. Last step status
String status = context.getLastExecutionStatus();
System.out.println("Last Status: " + status);

// 5. Execution time
long time = context.getExecutionTime();
System.out.println("Time: " + time + " ms");
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
()✅ 1️⃣ getLaunchMessage():-
👉 Kya karta hai:-
Workflow start hone pe jo UI me message show hota hai, wo return karta hai

✅ Code:-
String msg = context.getLaunchMessage();
System.out.println("Launch Message: " + msg);
🟢 Output:-
Launch Message: Workflow started successfully

✅ 2️⃣ setLaunchMessage():-
👉 Kya karta hai:-
Existing launch message ko replace karta hai

✅ Code:-
context.setLaunchMessage("Provisioning started...");
🟢 Output (UI):-
Provisioning started...

✅ 3️⃣ addLaunchMessage()
👉 Kya karta hai:-
Launch message me extra message add karta hai (append)

✅ Code:-
context.addLaunchMessage("Role assignment in progress...");
🟢 Output (UI):-
Workflow started successfully
Role assignment in progress...

✅ 4️⃣ addMessage():-
👉 Kya karta hai:-
Workflow case me message add karta hai (logs / UI messages)

✅ Code:-
context.addMessage("Provisioning plan created");
🟢 Output:-
Workflow Messages:-
- Provisioning plan created

✅ 5️⃣ getMessage()
👉 Kya karta hai:-
Stored / localized message return karta hai
✅ Code:-
String message = context.getMessage("provision.success");
System.out.println("Message: " + message);
🟢 Output:-
Message: Provisioning completed successfully

✅ 6️⃣ getProperty()
👉 Kya karta hai:-
Workflow ya system property ka value return karta hai
✅ Code:-
String env = context.getProperty("environment");
System.out.println("Environment: " + env);
🟢 Output:-
Environment: production

✅ 7️⃣ isProperty():-
👉 Kya karta hai:-
Check karta hai property exist karti hai ya nahi
✅ Code:-
boolean exists = context.isProperty("environment");
System.out.println("Property exists: " + exists);
🟢 Output:-
Property exists: true

✅ 8️⃣ commit():-
👉 Kya karta hai:-
Workflow ke changes database me save (permanent) karta hai
✅ Code:-
context.commit();
🟢 Output:-
Transaction committed successfully

✅ 9️⃣ rollback():-
👉 Kya karta hai:-
Workflow ke changes undo (revert) karta hai
✅ Code:-
context.rollback();
🟢 Output:-
Transaction rolled back
-----------------------------
🔥 Full Combined Example:-
// Launch message
context.setLaunchMessage("Workflow started");
context.addLaunchMessage("Processing request...");

// Add workflow message
context.addMessage("Provisioning initiated");

// Get property
String env = context.getProperty("environment");

// Check property
if (context.isProperty("environment")) {
    context.addMessage("Environment: " + env);
}

// Commit changes
context.commit();
🟢 Output:-
Workflow started
Processing request...
Provisioning initiated
Environment: production
Transaction committed successfully
