🔷 1️⃣ Workflow Info Methods:-
getWorkflow():-
👉 Current workflow object return karta hai

Object wf = context.getWorkflow();
System.out.println(wf);

🟢 Output:-
Workflow object: IdentityRequestWorkflow
---
()getWorkflowName():-
👉 Workflow ka naam return karta hai

String name = context.getWorkflowName();
System.out.println("Workflow Name: " + name);

🟢 Output:-
Workflow Name: IdentityRequestWorkflow
----
()getWorkflowDefinition():-
👉 Workflow ka full definition (XML/config) deta hai

Object def = context.getWorkflowDefinition();
System.out.println(def);

🟢 Output:-
<Workflow name="IdentityRequestWorkflow">...</Workflow>
----
()getApplication() / setApplication():-
👉 Application (jaise AD, SAP) get/set karta hai

Object app = context.getApplication();
System.out.println(app);

context.setApplication(app);

🟢 Output:-
Application: Active Directory
----
()getScope() / setScope():-
👉 Scope define karta hai (kis area / org ke liye workflow run hoga)

Object scope = context.getScope();
context.setScope(scope);

🟢 Output:-
Scope: IT Department
----
()getPopulation() / setPopulation():-
👉 Users ka group (population) get/set karta hai

Object pop = context.getPopulation();
context.setPopulation(pop);

🟢 Output:-
Population: All Employees
----
()getCreated() / getModified():-
👉 Object kab create / update hua

System.out.println(context.getCreated());
System.out.println(context.getModified());

🟢 Output:-
Created: 2026-03-01
Modified: 2026-03-10
----
()getCreatedBy() / getModifiedBy():-
👉 Kisne create / modify kiya

System.out.println(context.getCreatedBy());
System.out.println(context.getModifiedBy());

🟢 Output:-
Created By: admin
Modified By: manager1
----

()toXml():-
👉 Object ko XML me convert karta hai

String xml = context.toXml();
System.out.println(xml);

🟢 Output:-
<WorkflowCase>...</WorkflowCase>

👉 Nahi, context.toXml() ka output WorkflowContext ka XML nahi hota ❌
👉 Ye actually WorkflowCase / SailPoint object ka XML hota hai ✅
kyuki toxml() workflowcontext pe kaam nahi karta.

----
()fromXml(String xml):-
👉 XML se object banata hai

context.fromXml(xmlData);
🟢 Output:-
WorkflowCase loaded from XML

----
()toMap():-
👉 Object ko Map me convert karta hai

Map map = context.toMap();
System.out.println(map);

🟢 Output:-
{name=Workflow1, status=SUCCESS}

-----
()fromMap(Map map):-
👉 Map se object populate karta hai
context.fromMap(map);

🟢 Output:-
WorkflowCase populated from map
-----
()clone():-
👉 Object ka copy banata hai

Object copy = context.clone();
System.out.println(copy);

🟢 Output:-
Cloned WorkflowCase object
----------
()equals(Object obj):-
👉 Do objects same hain ya nahi

boolean eq = context.equals(copy);
System.out.println(eq);

🟢 Output:-
true
----
hashCode():-
👉 Object ka unique hash code

int hash = context.hashCode();
System.out.println(hash);

🟢 Output:-
12345678
------------------------
()toString():-
👉 Object ka string representation
System.out.println(context.toString());
🟢 Output:-
WorkflowCase[name=IdentityRequestWorkflow, status=SUCCESS]
-----------------------
()🔹 validate() ka real purpose:-
Check karta hai ki object valid state me hai ya nahi
Required fields missing to nahi
Data structure sahi hai ya nahi

🔹 WorkflowContext ke case me:-
👉 WorkflowContext khud:-
runtime object hai
temporary hai

👉 Isliye:-
validate() → indirectly WorkflowCase / internal data ko check karta hai

✅ Kya-kya check ho sakta hai:-

✔️ 1. Required data present hai ya nahi
identity present hai?
plan present hai?
arguments null to nahi?
✔️ 2. Object structure valid hai
ProvisioningPlan correct hai?
Workflow variables sahi type ke hain?
✔️ 3. Internal consistency
workflow state valid hai?
execution me koi missing dependency to nahi?
--------------------------------------------------
